an%20internal%20culture%20built%20on%20power%2C%20deference%2C%20and%20secrecy%2C%20where%20Mark%20Zuckerberg's%20employees%20allegedly%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-board-game-careless-people-sarah-wynn-williams-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20let%20him%20win%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20board%20games%2C%20where%20executives%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2025%2F03%2F09%2Fmeta-china-censorship-facebook-mark-zuckerberg%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereportedly%3C%2Fa%3E%20bent%20over%20backward%20to%20court%20the%20Chinese%20government%2C%20and%20where%20she%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Ftech%2Fsocial-media%2Ffacebook-alleges-harassment-sandberg-kaplan-sarah-wynn-williams-rcna195130%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20claims%3C%2Fa%3E%20Meta's%20top%20policy%20executive%2C%20Joel%20Kaplan%2C%20sexually%20harassed%20her.%20(Meta%20has%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fandymstone%2Fstatus%2F1899081966105813011%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20denied%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20allegations%20about%20Kaplan%2C%20saying%20an%20internal%20investigation%20found%20them%20%26quot%3Bmisleading%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bunfounded.%26quot%3B%20The%20company%20cleared%20Kaplan%20in%202017.%20Meta%20also%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.fb.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FSarah-Wynn-Williams-New-Book-Of-Old-News.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edocument%3C%2Fa%3E%20stating%20that%20some%20of%20Wynn-Williams'%20claims%20in%20the%20book%20about%20Meta's%20China%20and%20Myanmar%20operations%20were%20%26quot%3Bold%20news%26quot%3B).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20Wynn-Williams%20also%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2025%2F03%2F09%2Fmeta-china-censorship-facebook-mark-zuckerberg%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20filed%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20whistleblower%20complaint%20with%20the%20SEC%20over%20Meta's%20dealings%20in%20China%2C%20alleging%20the%20company%20misled%20investors%2C%20and%20went%20to%20great%20lengths%20to%20please%20the%20Chinese%20government%20in%20a%20failed%20attempt%20to%20launch%20Facebook%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20all%20pushed%20by%20an%20employee%20terminated%20eight%20years%20ago%20for%20poor%20performance.%20We%20do%20not%20operate%20our%20services%20in%20China%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Meta%20Spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20no%20secret%20we%20were%20once%20interested%20in%20doing%20so%20as%20part%20of%20Facebook's%20effort%20to%20connect%20the%20world.%20This%20was%20widely%20reported%20beginning%20a%20decade%20ago.%20We%20ultimately%20opted%20not%20to%20go%20through%20with%20the%20ideas%20we'd%20explored%2C%20which%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20announced%20in%202019.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20leaving%20Meta%2C%20Wynn-Williams%20shifted%20her%20focus%20to%20AI%20policy%2C%20including%20participating%20in%20a%20dialogue%20between%20US%20and%20Chinese%20experts%20on%20AI%20and%20military%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20its%20release%2C%20%3Cem%3ECareless%20People%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-favorite-president-andrew-jackson-new-book-says-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20made%20headlines%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20drawn%20a%20swift%2C%20aggressive%20response%20from%20Meta.%20Multiple%20current%20and%20former%20employees%2C%20including%20some%20featured%20in%20the%20book%2C%20have%20publicly%20disputed%20Wynn-Williams'%20claims%2C%20calling%20them%20exaggerated%20or%20false.%20The%20company%20has%20gone%20after%20her%20in%20an%20unprecedented%20way%2C%20arguing%20that%20she%20violated%20a%20nondisparagement%20agreement%20and%20securing%20an%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.fb.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FArbitration-Interim-Award.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20emergency%20arbitration%20ruling%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20restricts%20her%20ability%20to%20speak%20publicly%20about%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20book%20is%20a%20mix%20of%20out-of-date%20and%20previously%20reported%20claims%20about%20the%20company%20and%20false%20accusations%20about%20our%20executives%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Meta%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSarah%20Wynn-Williams%20was%20fired%20for%20poor%20performance%20and%20toxic%20behavior%2C%20and%20an%20investigation%20at%20the%20time%20determined%20she%20made%20misleading%20and%20unfounded%20allegations%20of%20harassment.%20Since%20then%2C%20she%20has%20been%20paid%20by%20anti-Facebook%20activists%2C%20and%20this%20is%20simply%20a%20continuation%20of%20that%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20continued.%20%26quot%3BWhistleblower%20status%20protects%20communications%20to%20the%20government%2C%20not%20disgruntled%20activists%20trying%20to%20sell%20books.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20reached%20for%20comment%20about%20the%20arbitration%20ruling%2C%20a%20legal%20representative%20for%20Wynn-Williams%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BBecause%20of%20an%20order%20dated%2012%20March%20sought%20by%20Meta%2C%20Ms%20Wynn-Williams%20has%20been%20prevented%20from%20providing%20comment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlatiron%20Books%2C%20Wynn-William's%20publisher%2C%20provided%20BI%20with%20the%20following%20statement%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20arbitration%20order%20has%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3Eno%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20impact%20on%20Macmillan.%20However%2C%20we%20are%20appalled%20by%20Meta's%20tactics%20to%20silence%20our%20author%20through%20the%20use%20of%20a%20non-disparagement%20clause%20in%20a%20severance%20agreement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20be%20clear%26quot%3B%2C%20Marlena%20Bittner%2C%20the%20publisher's%20director%20of%20publicity%20told%20BI%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20arbitrator's%20order%20makes%20no%20reference%20to%20the%20claims%20within%20%3Cem%3ECareless%20People%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20book%20went%20through%20a%20thorough%20editing%20and%20vetting%20process%2C%20and%20we%20remain%20committed%20to%20publishing%20important%20books%20such%20as%20this.%20We%20will%20absolutely%20continue%20to%20support%20and%20promote%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWynn-Williams%20avoided%20directly%20answering%20some%20of%20BI's%20questions%20about%20the%20company's%20accusations%20against%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPartly%20driven%20by%20the%20buzz%20generated%20by%20Meta's%20own%20attempts%20to%20suppress%20it%2C%20%3Cem%3ECareless%20People%20%3C%2Fem%3Eranked%20among%20the%20top%2010%20bestsellers%20on%20Amazon%20in%20the%20US%20when%20this%20article%20was%20published.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBelow%20are%20excerpts%20from%20BI's%20interview%20with%20Wynn-Williams%2C%20edited%20for%20clarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20lot%20of%20people%20were%20surprised%20when%20this%20book%20was%20announced.%20Why%20did%20you%20keep%20it%20under%20wraps%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20if%20you%20see%20the%20reaction%20that's%20happened%20since%2C%20I%20think%20that%20explains%20the%20decision.%20When%20I%20decided%20to%20tell%20my%20story%20and%20speak%20out%20about%20all%20these%20true%20experiences%20that%20are%20in%20the%20book%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20story%20would%20be%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20crazy%20when%20we%20live%20in%20a%20world%20where%20Meta%20is%20doubling%20down%20on%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20purports%20to%20be%20about%20supporting%20free%20speech.%20I%20thought%3A%20I%20want%20this%20out%20in%20the%20world%E2%80%94and%20so%20that's%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20for%20doing%20it%20that%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20left%20Facebook%20in%202017.%20Why%20did%20you%20decide%20to%20release%20it%20now%2C%20after%20all%20these%20years%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20I%20think%20we're%20on%20the%20cusp%20of%20this%20new%20era%20of%20technology.%20We're%20stepping%20into%20this%20AI%20era%2C%20and%20at%20a%20high%20level%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20the%20mistakes%20that%20were%20made%20during%20the%20social%20media%20era%20to%20be%20applied%20to%20the%20AI%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20things%20that%20I've%20worked%20on%20since%20leaving%20%5BMeta%5D%20is%20the%20US-China%20AI%20dialogue%20on%20AI%20in%20weapons.%20So%2C%20I%20really%20understand%20the%20existential%20nature%20of%20AI.%20I%20also%20understand%20these%20people%20and%20how%20decisions%20are%20made.%20That's%20why%2C%20as%20we%20go%20into%20this%20new%20era%2C%20we%20have%20to%20do%20it%20better.%20China%20is%20such%20a%20big%20part%20of%20the%20story%20of%20AI.%20It's%20this%20growing%20strategic%20rivalry%20and%20how%20technology%20is%20so%20central%20to%20that%20rivalry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20this%20company%20has%20been%20doing%20things%20in%20the%20shadows%20for%20so%20long%20with%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%2C%20and%20their%20line%20is%2C%20oh%2C%20you%20know%2C%20we%20tried%20to%20get%20our%20services%20%5Binto%20China%5D%20and%20we%20told%20you%20in%202019%20that%20didn't%20happen.%20Have%20a%20look%20at%20how%20much%20of%20%5BMeta's%5D%20revenue%20comes%20from%20China%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20%2418%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(Editor's%20note%3A%20According%20to%20Meta's%202024%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fd18rn0p25nwr6d.cloudfront.net%2FCIK-0001326801%2Fa8eb8302-b52c-4db5-964f-a2d796c05f4b.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20annual%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company%20made%20%2418.35%20billion%20from%20China%2C%20primarily%20through%20resellers%20serving%20Chinese%20advertisers%20targeting%20global%20users.)%20So%20it%20seems%20that%20everyone%20is%20operating%20under%20the%20false%20notion%20that%20Meta%20is%20not%20operating%20in%20China%20when%20actually%2C%20it%20is%20fundamental%20to%20its%20current%20valuation%2C%20it's%20fundamental%20to%20its%20future%20growth.%20And%20we%20don't%20talk%20openly%20about%20it%20at%20the%20very%20time%20that%20we're%20about%20to%20enter%20this%20new%20AI%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20was%20your%20process%20for%20writing%20this%20book%3F%20How%20long%20did%20it%20take%20you%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20was%20off%20and%20on.%20It%20was%20something%20that%20I%20felt%20there%20was%20a%20growing%20need%20and%20importance%20%5Bfor%5D.%20It's%20a%20memoir%3B%20it's%20my%20story%3B%20and%20it's%20a%20true%20story%20that%20is%20also%20underpinned%20by%20evidence%2C%20and%2C%20further%20to%20that%2C%20underpinned%20%5Bby%20my%5D%20filing%20with%20the%20SEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%5BMy%20writing%20process%5D%20wasn't%20a%20linear%20thing.%20There%20were%20moments%20when%20something%20would%20happen%2C%20there%20would%20be%20a%20headline%20about%20China%2C%20and%20I'd%20think%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20so%20different%20if%20people%20knew%20the%20truth.%26quot%3B%20Or%20there'd%20be%20a%20headline%20about%20something%20bad%20happening%20with%20teens%20using%20Instagram%2C%20and%20I'd%20think%20%26quot%3BOh%20God.%26quot%3B%20The%20story%20they%20were%20telling%20was%20departing%20more%20and%20more%20from%20the%20truth%20and%20it%20seemed%20more%20and%20more%20imperative%20that%20the%20truth%20was%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMeta%20spokesperson%20Andy%20Stone%20has%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.threads.net%2F%40andymstone%2Fpost%2FDG_55dnMiD0%3Fxmt%3DAQGzCRSfUQw9FJp6M48uJFSUC4PH__jaTp6Jv8dxxG0-hQ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Esaid%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20that%20your%20book%20wasn't%20fact-checked%20and%20that%20nobody%20reached%20out%20to%20Meta%20for%20comment.%20Did%20you%20get%20the%20book%20fact-checked%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20Meta's%20problem%20is%20using%20this%20to%20not%20answer%20the%20questions%20themselves.%20What%20I%20would%20love%20is%20for%20us%20not%20to%20fall%20into%20the%20distraction.%20There's